cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.SY, cs.CV, cs.ME 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.RO (Robotics) - The paper focuses on model-based whole-body control in legged robots and identification of inertial parameters for a leg of the MIT Cheetah 3 robot. 
2. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The paper discusses the use of statistical methods for identification of inertial parameters and optimization through semidefinite programming. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper deals with system identification and physical-consistency constraints on inertial parameters, which are important in control of robotic systems. 
4. cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) - While not the main focus, the paper mentions the use of vision-based methods for measuring the mass distribution of the leg. 
5. cs.ME (Mechanical Engineering) - The paper deals with the physical properties of a legged robot and identification of its inertial parameters, which are important in mechanical engineering applications.
